The article is a message from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, reporting that the President has issued an Executive Order authorizing additional sanctions with respect to Iran. The order takes steps to address the threat posed by Iran's actions and policies, particularly in relation to the development of petroleum resources and the evasion of international sanctions. The order authorizes the Secretary of the Treasury and the Secretary of State to impose sanctions on persons involved in significant financial transactions with certain Iranian entities, as well as those engaged in the purchase or acquisition of petroleum, petroleum products, or petrochemical products from Iran. The order also provides for various actions to be taken against sanctioned persons, including restrictions on financial dealings, procurement, and imports. The Secretary of the Treasury is delegated the authority to carry out the purposes of the order. The order was effective as of July 31, 2012.